  "prompt": "How do you say goodbye to a dying loved one?",
  "response": "Saying goodbye to a dying loved one is incredibly difficult and deeply personal. Here are some gentle suggestions:\n\n1. Be present\n- Hold their hand\n- Sit quietly with them\n- Offer comfort through touch and presence\n\n2. Express your feelings\n- Tell them \"I love you\"\n- Share memories you cherish\n- Say thank you for what they've meant to you\n- Tell them it's okay to let go\n\n3. Listen\n- If they want to talk, be a compassionate listener\n- Allow them to express their feelings\n- Don't force conversation if they're tired\n\n4. Offer reassurance\n- Let them know they won't be forgotten\n- Comfort them about their family/loved ones\n- Assure them they are loved\n\n5. Consider spiritual/personal comfort\n- Pray together if they're religious\n- Play meaningful music\n- Read something special to them\n\n6. Practical considerations\n- Say anything you need to say\n- Resolve any lingering conflicts\n- Make peace with your relationship\n\n7. Take care of yourself\n- It's emotionally exhausting\n- Allow yourself to grieve\n- Seek support from others\n\nRemember, there's no \"perfect\" way to do this. Being genuine, loving, and present is what matters most.",
